<subSubSection lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1659,2008]" lastBlockId="42.[151,1436,151,247]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1840,1864]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." box="[324,629,1839,1863]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
believed that several records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1012,1123,1840,1864]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admete">
<emphasis box="[1012,1025,1841,1864]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1042,1123,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">admete</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Alcock 1899; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephenson, W." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="11 - 26" refId="ref52976" refString="Stephenson, W. (1976) Notes on Indo-West-Pacific Portunids (Decapoda, Portunidae) in the Smithsonian Institution. Crustaceana, 31 (1), 11 - 26." type="journal article" year="1976">Stephenson 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Basson, P. W. &amp; Burchard, J. E. &amp; Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G." box="[221,431,1876,1900]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refId="ref45702" refString="Basson, P. W., Burchard, J. E., Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G. (1977) Biotopes of the Western Arabian Gulf: Marine life and environments of Saudi Arabia. ARAMCO, Dept. of Loss Prevention and environmental affairs, Dhahran: 289 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Basson 
<emphasis box="[309,358,1876,1900]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">et al</emphasis>
. 1977
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Titgen, R. H." box="[442,578,1876,1900]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" refId="ref53402" refString="Titgen, R. H. (1982) The systematics and ecology of the Decapods of Dubai, and their zoogeographic relationships to the Persian Gulf and the Western Indian Ocean. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Texas A &amp; M University, 292 pp." type="book" year="1982">Titgen 1982</bibRefCitation>
) from the Persian Gulf were most probably based upon misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,274,1912,1936]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[151,164,1913,1936]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[181,274,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1861" box="[291,509,1912,1936]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[291,509,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Thalamita savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[813,925,1912,1936]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admete">
<emphasis box="[813,826,1913,1936]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[844,925,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">admete</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its sympatric congener in the Persian Gulf. Detailed taxonomic remarks distinguishing these two species have been provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov (1998: 270</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 4). They discussed on the distribution of the species in Indian Ocean and mentioned that the record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1861" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" order="Decapoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis box="[1415,1428,1985,2008]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,244,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the east coast of Africa and from 
<collectingCountry box="[686,785,151,175]" name="Tanzania" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[828,993,151,175]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="158 - 164" refId="ref51316" refString="Nobili, G. (1905 a) Decapodes nouveaux des cotes d'Arabie et du Golfe Persique (Diagnoses preliminaires). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 11, 158 - 164." type="journal article" year="1905">Nobili (1905a)</bibRefCitation>
is doubtful. An ongoing revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[228,343,188,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Thalamita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[228,343,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Thalamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is being performed by Vassily Spiridonov, which will hopefully resolve the taxonomic and distribution problems of these two species.
</paragraph>
